cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.SE 

The paper deals with developing robust smoothing algorithms for dynamical processes, which is a topic that falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of sparsity constraints and regularization techniques also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). The iterative estimators and convergence analysis are related to numerical analysis (cs.NA), while the simulated tests indicate a potential connection to software engineering (cs.SE).
